  <prompt>
    Implement the static-prefix composition (~6K tokens, byte-stable for prompt-cache hit) per architecture §6.2 + §10.2. Compose in stable order: persona → trust-frame injection (077) → tool definitions → workspace digest → layered context cards (076) → user preferences snapshot → glossary. Output must be BYTE-STABLE across turns within a session unless one of the underlying block contents changes. Cache-hit produces 50% discount + 80% faster TTFT per architecture §10.2.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in prompt-cache cost optimization + byte-stable composition + ADR-014 caching invariants.</role>

  <goal>
    Static-prefix composition method (likely in `SprkChatAgentFactory` or `PlaybookChatContextProvider`) produces ~6K tokens deterministically. Composition order is stable. Block-level recomposition only when a block's contents change. Token budget enforcement via `PromptBudgetTracker`. Open Question §12.1.1 documented (recently-discussed flag flip handling) — initial implementation places recently-discussed in dynamic suffix to maximize cache hit rate; flag in code comment + notes/handoffs/.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer.</role>

  <goal>
    Static prefix ≤6K tokens byte-stable; LayeredContextCardBuilder cards positioned in prefix; recently-discussed flag deferred to dynamic suffix per open-question resolution. Build + existing tests pass.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per architecture §6.2 (per-turn prompt assembly) + §10.2 (cost model with cache) + §10.3 (cache hit rate). The static prefix is the cacheable portion; the dynamic suffix is per-turn. Open Question §12.1.1: "does per-turn recently-discussed flag flip defeat caching?" Resolution: place recently-discussed in dynamic suffix (downgrades to non-cached part); maximizes static-prefix cache hit. This is documented in code + notes/handoffs/ for future benchmark validation.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/SprkChatAgentFactory.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PlaybookChatContextProvider.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Memory/PromptBudgetTracker.cs</file>
